GRTSource.description: Lists Features available to devices and their descriptions
GRTSource.title: Feature Descriptions

row.cell: The product supports CallManager and LSC certificates of RSA key sizes 3072/4096
Phone supports the use of Activation Code for Onboarding
The phone supports audible message waiting indicator tone (stutter tone or other)
Phone supports Authenticated Contact Search using client certificate authentication, which is the LSC of the supported phone

Choose one of the following options to activate the Auto Answer feature for this directory number: Auto Answer Off <Default>, Auto Answer with headset, Auto Answer with speakerphone (Intercom). Note : Make sure that the headset or speakerphone is not disabled when you choose Auto Answer with headset or Auto Answer with speakerphone.
This allow device to auto register to CallManager. This is CCM Admin only.

The AAR For Insufficient Bandwidth feature, as the extension of the AAR, provides a mechanism to automatically fall back to reroute the call through PSTN or other network by using an alternate number when the call is blocked by Call Manager due to insufficient location bandwidth, such that the caller does not need to hang up and redial the called party again. This is CCM Admin only.
The phone is capable of automatically rolling over to another line when the Max Number of Calls for a line has been reached, and a new call is requested
Supports Binary Floor Control Protocol (BFCP) for devices registered to Cisco Unified Communications Manager.
Busy lamp field speed-dial using URI as destination (new for SD-GA).
BLF Speed Dial: device supports Busy Lamp Field (BLF key) with Speed Dial functionality, and optionally Call Pickup (parameter = 1). Leave parameter blank if Call Pickup is not supported with BLF.
The phone has a built in conference bridge.
To show whether device is control by CTI or not.

Device supports Call Bubble Collapsing feature. This feature allows device to show a single call bubble for multiple calls on the line which have same Global Call Identifier, in the cases such as Conference, CBarge.

This is a service which allows priority calls to be placed and for properly validated users to pre-empt lower priority phone calls. The authenticated user can preempt calls either to targeted stations or through fully subscribed TDM trunks. With this capability, high-ranking personnel can be assured of communication to critical organizations and personnel during network stress situations such as a national emergency or degraded network situations. MLPP pre-emption means you can receive an MLPP call.

This is a service which allows priority calls to be placed and for properly validated users to pre-empt lower priority phone calls. The authenticated user can preempt calls either to targeted stations or through fully subscribed TDM trunks. With this capability, high-ranking personnel can be assured of communication to critical organizations and personnel during network stress situations such as a national emergency or degraded network situations. MLPP precedence means you can make an MLPP call.

Choose the appropriate call-waiting settings. This field determines whether this directory number uses call waiting when a line is busy (On), responds with a busy signal (Off), or uses the system-wide default setting (Default). The value that you choose applies to all devices that are using this directory number.
Cisco Unified Communications Manager will use the configured TimerRegExpires value from associated SIP Profile If device supports this feature, otherwise, the configured value will be ignored.
Supports connected transfer and conference feature
Indication for devices registered to Cisco Unified Communications Manager whether it is capable of suportting crypto session parameters. e.g. wsh.
Parameter Value includs 0 for JAR,1 for CSV. Devices without this feature are expected to support the default 0 for JAR
The phone supports caching of digest password
CCM acting as UAS : Ability to challenge a UAC for credentials . When UAC presents a Authorization header , ability to verify the MD5 hash as defined in RFC3261 and RFC 2617 (new for SD-GA).

The phone supports the Do Not Disturb (DND) feature which disables ringing on the device when used. Calls coming in while the phone has DND enabled are subject to the DND Option for handling the call: 0 = Ringer Off; 1 = Reject Call; 2 - Ringer Off, Call Reject, Use Common Profile all valid. If a phone does not support both options, it should specify the supported option in the parameter (0 or 1).

Indicates that the product incorporates hardware, software, and messaging protocol support for managing separate Active and Inactive Firmware banks along with the associated background download and independent cut-over control handling. (Must support SIP message version containing both Active and Inactive Load Information specifications.)
The phone is capable of operating on both IP (WLAN) and GSM networks; parameter value of 1 if Smart Client capable, otherwise 0 or empty
ECDHE support with AES256/128 with ECDSA signing
The product supports TLS_ECDHE_ECDSA with AES256/AES128 GCMSHA384 Cipher for TLS Connections
ECDHE support with AES256/128 with RSA signing
The product supports TLS_ECDHE_RSA with AES256/AES128 GCMSHA384 Cipher for TLS Connections
Supports Early Offer for devices registered to Cisco Unified Communications Manager.
Supports enhanced Message Waiting Indicators and status
Can your phone connect to a Cisco IP Phone 7914 Expansion Module or some other future Expansion Modules.
This device allow user to login with their id and password . There is no special code in firmware. This is purely marketing driven.
Support Extension Mobility Cross Cluster or not
Supports Feature Control Policy for phones as the method of controlling which Softkeys are enabled on the phone display. This feature is not compatible with the Softkey Template feature.
This feature allows the user to use any phone template which has the same number of buttons as that of the model

Designates support and type of configuration file encryption. A value 1 indicates AES and 2 indicates RC4. A 1 or 2 should be specified in the textbox against the field in this miscellaneous phone features page (new for SD-GA).

Uses Traffic Class Label (TCL) to dynamically instruct the SIP end point to mark its Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) per call, based on Video Promotion Policy. The Video Promotion Policy can be configured through service parameter - Video Call QoS Marking Policy.
The product has an internal HTTP server that will respond if port 80 at the root level.
Enter the custom software for the Cisco IP Phone. The value that you enter overrides the default value for the current model.

The phone button template determines the configuration of buttons on a phone and identifies which feature (line, speed dial, and so on) is used for each button. The value that you enter overrides the default value for this type of device. Format=no of buttons on base phone,total no of buttons including expansion module
The product supports softkey templates. Remember, softkey templates cannot be customized per product.
After a holding party put a call on hold for certain time, it will be notified with a hold reversion notification ring and prompt display message.
This feature restricts/presents the calling/connected information based on the parties involved in the call. (Obsolete)
Indicates whether the device is capable of downloading and using Hotspot Profile configured in UCM Administration.
The device supports both PLAR capability (digit-less offhook reporting to CM) as well as the connectivity restrictions associated with Hotline devices.
Supports the features and functionality provided for IMS-integrated Mobile devices.
The product supports IP Phone Services. This means that all device table records in the database, will have a corresponding TelecasterService record.
This feature allows user to have Manager/Assistant functionality on the phone.
Immersive Video Support for TelePresence Devices
Telepresence devices support immersive video calls.
The phone supports the intercom feature. Devices with phone button templates must also have an intercom button on the template to use the feature
The call can be joined across lines

Designates the maximum value for device.tkkeyauthority for this phone. A value 1 indicates Symmetric and 2 indicates Full. A 1:x or 2 should be specified in the textbox against this field in the miscellaneous phone features page;x would be 128 or 256 depending on the number of bits (new for SD-GA).

Use this field only if you do not want the directory number shown on the line appearance. Enter text that identifies this directory number for a line/phone combination. Suggested entries include boss's name, department's name, or other appropriate information to identify multiple directory numbers to secretary/assistant who monitors multiple directory numbers. Setting applies only to the current device unless you check the check box at right and click the Propagate selected button. (The check box at right displays only if other devices share this directory number.)
Supports option to turn missed call logging on or off for individual lines or the whole device

Use this field to configure the handset lamp illumination policy. Choose one of the following options: Use System Policy (The directory number refers to the service parameter "Message Waiting Lamp Policy" setting.), Always Light, Never Light. Setting applies only to the current device unless you check the check box at right and click the Propagate selected button. (The check box at right displays only if other devices share this directory number.)
This allow user to push a button on the phone to mark the call malicious in CallDetailedRecord.(Obsolete)

Join Across Line behavior is necessary for normal operation and CTI. Join Across Lines is always on and related configuration options are ignored. If Join Across Lines is a configurable option for the phone, use the Join Across Lines feature instead.
This feature allows to set the MIC on the supported Phones.
This define the max calls per line (Not Implemented)

Specifies the maximum length in bytes of the User ID (AuthName) used for authentication and authorization by the device. Use Parameter value to specify maximum supported length. Not needed if device supports the full 128 byte AuthName.
Supports mobility features including single number reach, dual mode and IVR access (version 6.0 or later)
This allow 3rd parties to listen in on phone conversation.
Device that can display multiple call simultaneously. Edit box format: 200:4:2 (Max calls per device:default max calls per line:default busy trigger).
Multiple Codecs Support in Answer SDP

Cisco Unified Communications Manager shall support passing multiple codecs in the answer for the following call scenarios: mid-call re-invites, initial call-setup using early offer and initial call setup (early offer to delayed offer).
Multiple levels of XML configuration data (vendor configuration)
The product supports Music On Hold.
NOT IMPLEMENTED - Serial Number and Release Key Management for Tandberg Endpoint
Cisco Unified Communications Manager will determine if Serial Number and Release Key Management required for an Endpoint.

To specify the audio source that is played when the network initiates a hold action, click the drop-down arrow and choose an audio source from the list that displays. If you do not choose an audio source, Cisco CallManager uses the audio source that is defined in the device pool or the system default if the device pool does not specify an audio source ID. Note : You define audio sources in the Music On Hold Audio Source Configuration window. For access, choose Service > Music On Hold.
The model has past the End of Support date and is being deprecated. This model is no longer supported by Cisco Unified Communications Manager and will not able to register
This feature designates alternate script for a locale is perfered on the Phone.
Phone attached to a Gateway (Like Chalice)
VGC Phones (Chalice) are created like endpoints of a VG248 gateway. This field is use to distinguish this device from other phones.
This allow administrator to modify the phone template.
Supports subscription of Presence information from Call Manager (new for SD-GA)
This feature allow user to control their phone call privacy and it only apply to shared line phone.
This specifies RTP Payload for DTMF Digits, Telephony Tones and Telephony Signals
This allow user to record audio stream.
Some devices will support remote lock feature where the device can be locked if the device is registered, if device is not registered the device will be locked the next time it registers
Some devices will support remote wipe feature where all its data can be erased if the device is registered, if device is not registered the contents will be erased the next time it registers
This means that product requires DTMF reception.
Device support for being located off premise (off corporate network).
Restrict Maximum Call and Busy Trigger
Phone configuration is restricted to MaxNumCalls:BusyTrigger as specified in the parameter (e.g., 2:1 means MaxNumCalls = 2, BusyTrigger = 1)

Use this field to configure the ring setting for the line appearance when an incoming call is received and no other active calls exist on that device. Choose one of the following options: Use system default, Disable, Flash only, Ring once, Ring.
The product supports SHA-512 Digital Signature.

SIP OAuth flag can be enabled only for the Phone security profile of particular models(Jabber-BOT,CSF,TAB,TCT and Universal device Template). The phone (Jabber devices of SIP protocol)connects to the call manager using the TLS protocol.
Supports TCP on SIP Phone model (new for SD-GA)
The product supports SRTP_AEAD_AES_128_GCM Cipher for SRTP Connections
The product supports SRTP_AEAD_AES_256_GCM Cipher for SRTP Connections
Seamless TCP Reconnect After Connections Drop or Roaming

Supports the feature to delay session tear-down and also to permit session resume after TCP disconnect or reconnect resulting from network hand-off conditions. When supported,this parameter specifies the default value for 'Time to Wait for Seamless Reconnect After TCP Drop or Roaming'. This field has default value of 5 sec and is configurable to any value between 0 to 300 secs.
Allows connection from SSH client. The SSH connection helps in capturing debug information from phones (new for SD-GA).
Supports secure tone indication when end-to-end secure (encrypted) media is established
This option when enabled configures the phone to do call signaling integrity. The phone connects to the call manager using the TLS protocol with SHA authentication algorithm.
Supports download of Cisco Unified Communications Manager constructed configuration files that are encrypted and signed.

This option when enabled configures the phone to do call signaling integrity and privacy. The phone connects to the call manager using the Transport Layer Security (TLS) protocol with SHA authentication and AES-128 encryption algorithms. (NOTE: In Parche we are not going to publish this option.)
Allows mobile user to send calls to a RIM device using it's (SIP) shared line Mobility key.
Can share DN with another device.
Uses forward on device failure (use by CTI).
Display text labels for speeddial buttons.
The single button barge feature is supported
Indicates whether the device is capable of enabling single registration by default when registering with Cisco Unified Communications Manager
This feature allows the user to use any phone button template configured on the system
Specify Types of TFTP Config Files

Supports download of Call Manager constructed config files via TFTP. A value of 0 indicates don't build TFTP files. A value of 1 indicates 'BIN/TXT' for legacy format and 7905/12 SIP phones that use binary and 7940/60 SIP Phones that use text format. A value of 2 indicates 'XML'- TNP and other phones support XML. A value 3 indicates 'BIN/TXT/XML'- Phones supporting both 1 and 2. Prior to 7.0 release, Param 3 is the default value. No parameter indicates 'BIN/TXT/XML'-build all (assumed by TFTP code). In 7.0 and later releases, Param 2 is the default. Only XML files are built if no parameter (or no supports feature entry) is present.
This allow user to view the status of the list of users they are monitoring.(Obsolete)
Phone being able to interact with CAPF to acquire Locally Significant Certficates (LSCs) (new for SD-GA).
CCM acting as server side : Ability to present its certificate to client. Verify the certificate and Subject name of Client. RFC 2246 (new for SD-GA).
CCM acting as server : Ability to present its certificate to client. RFC2246 (not in SD-GA).
Endpoints supporting TLSv1.2. This protocol version supports stronger security and meets Common Criteria requirements.

A Trusted Device is a Cisco device or a third-party device that has passed Cisco security criteria for trusted connections. This includes but is not limited to signaling/media encryption, platform hardening, and assurance. If a device is trusted, a secure icon (when supported) displays, a secure tone (when supported) is played, and the device may provide other features or indicators related to secure calls. To specify the audio source that plays when a user initiates a hold action, click the drop-down arrow and choose an audio source from the list that displays. If you do not choose an audio source, Cisco CallManager uses the audio source that is defined in the device pool or the system default if the device pool does not specify an audio source ID. Note : You define audio sources in the Music On Hold Audio Source Configuration window. For access, choose Service > Music On Hold.
